The Assignment

The Nigerian Government has committed $1.2 billion USD to achieving the United Nations Millennium Development Goals. Matching grants are given to Local Government Areas (LGAs) for approved projects and programmes geared towards reducing poverty and improving education and health. To promote the use of data in the local planning process, a rigorous, geo-referenced, baseline facility inventory was conducted for the entire country. The objective was to collect data for all of Nigerias health, education and water facilities. The result is this online portal, the Nigeria MDG Information System (NMIS) see http://nmis.mdgs.gov.ng/about.

Using this rich dataset, we will assess a few key development statistics, previously unknowable.

Set up

Load needed packages and user defined functions.

library(knitr)
library(rmarkdown)
library(plyr)
library(ggplot2)

# function to check NAs in a data frame
NAcheck <- function(data) {
  NAs <- sum(is.na(data))
  print(paste("NAs:", NAs))  # count NA's
  if (NAs > 0) 
    data[which(is.na(data)), ]  # Show NA's, if any.
  cc <- complete.cases(data)  # logical for each case (row)
  print(paste("Complete Cases:", all(cc)))  # Given a set of logical values, are all TRUE?
}

# function to return string w/o leading or trailing whitespace
trim <- function (x) gsub("^\\s+|\\s+$", "", x)

Calculate numbers of doctors and nurses percapita and per square kilometer

state$nurses_pp <- state$num_nurses_fulltime/state$state_pop_2006
state$nurses_psk <- state$num_nurses_fulltime/state$state_area_sq_km
state$doctors_pp <- state$num_doctors_fulltime/state$state_pop_2006
state$doctors_psk <- state$num_doctors_fulltime/state$state_area_sq_km
